findings.findings:
The S3 bucket is configured with public-read access, which exposes sensitive data to the entire internet. Vulnerable Code: resource "aws_s3_bucket" "data" {
  bucket = "company-backups"
  acl    = "public-read"
} Suggested Fix: resource "aws_s3_bucket" "data" {
  bucket = "company-backups"
  acl    = "private"
  control_object_ownership = true
}

Security group allows SSH traffic from any IP address. This increases the risk of brute-force attacks. Vulnerable Code: ingress {
  from_port   = 22
  to_port     = 22
  protocol    = "tcp"
  cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
} Suggested Fix: ingress {
  from_port   = 22
  to_port     = 22
  protocol    = "tcp"
  cidr_blocks = ["10.0.0.0/16"] # Use your VPC CIDR
}

Sensitive credentials found in plaintext within the terraform configuration. Vulnerable Code: provider "aws" {
  region     = "us-east-1"
  access_key = "AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE"
  secret_key = "wJalrXUtnFEMI/K7MDENG/bPxRfiCYEXAMPLEKEY"
} Suggested Fix: provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
  # Use Environment Variables or AWS Vault instead
}
